content.description: Climb the dihedral hand crack until you can step right onto the face about 1/3 of the way up.  Face climb the rest of the way, folowing the bolts.  Good rock.
content.protection: Pro to 3", 5 bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Starts on the right crack in the back of the alcove, left of Dogfish.

content.description: Steep prow at far left side of Funhouse alcove. Mostly casual climbing to a short V6 crux. Sends have generally skipped the mid crux bolt as it interrupts the climbing but makes for a good means to hangdog/work it.
content.protection: 11 Draws. Anchors below lip and above lip.

content.description: Start on Tigerbill on the far left ledge of the funhouse alcove. Follow to it's fourth bolt, then merg right onto steep white blocks over a cave. Numerous technical moves lead to an exciting finish.

A long overlooked line from the 90’s that received an upgrade in spring 2021. You no longer need to scramble across a ledge to start the line. Begin on the left side of the notable prow on a pronounced 3 foot diving board of rock. Pull a move or two and it quickly turns casual up to the impending overhang. Once reached, motor through steep buckets past three bolts (the crux is constantly clipping). Excellent position. For an added bonus, you can navigate past the anchors (right, then left, or direct up) to tack on a 5.12 boulder problem using a kind of weird extra bolt. Go to the mega jug up and left, then victory whip.
Climb the right of the dihedral a few feet to gain the finger crack to the left.  Follow this up to the first bolt.  Then climb the face and slab to the anchors.  Good rock.
content.protection: 4 bolts, medium to large nuts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: Right in the middle/back of Funhouse Alcove.  Start on the right side of the dihedral, then left to the finger crack.

content.description: Climb hand crack low for 30 feet, stay left at the tree into the crux offwidth to slab finish.
content.location: Same start as Tomiko right of Gomerwood.

content.description: I start on Tigerbill, heading right when it gets slabby.  Whatever way you choose, you need to end up at the base of the steep left-angling hand crack.  Some nice steep crack moves take you to a small tree.  Sling it and head right to the bolts.  Good rock, if you go this way.
content.protection: Pro to 3", 2 bolt anchor.  Bolts, too, if starting on either bolted line.
content.location: This line climbs the left arching crack up high.  Start either on Funhouse to the right, in the vegetated broken chossy finger crack (the original line), or on Tigerbill to the left (the best way)

content.description: Start on thin vertical/slabby face climbing, heading left near the top of the first section.  Head back right as you scramble up to the base of the headwall.  Then, head up on excellent moves and good rock past 3 or 4 bolts.
content.protection: Bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Maybe take a .75 camalot for between the first two bolts of the headwall near the top.
content.location: In the middle of the right facing wall, just left of Gomerwood.

content.description: Clip the first bolt and work around the left side of the very chossy section to gain the ledge.  Here, the climb may be considered a little runout because if you fail to clip the second bolt, you will deck.  From the ledge, head up on pretty good rock and enjoyable face climbing, pulling a small roof along the way.
content.protection: 6 bolts, 2 bolt anchor.  Rap or lower.
content.location: On the right side of the alcove, this route starts on a bolt below a ledge.

content.description: Previously to be avoided but with a 2021 update: stickclip a high bolt or just go for it on some questionable jugs. Pull into a corner and eventually run it out on very moderate climbing. Pass an old anchor (on your right) and pull over a little roof with a bolt. Continue up more 4th/5th class to a bolted anchor beneath a corner.OPTIONAL “mountaineers exit”- exit left and up a 4th class loose face. There is a bolt above a cedar tree on your right. DO NOT GO LEFT into choss city. Scramble or use the tree past some pitiful rock to top out. Belay from an old piton and a tree on top.
content.protection: 6 bolts, 2 bolt anchor. Rap, lower, exit left or continue to the summit and walk back down the gulley. .
content.location: Starting on the left side of the biggest prow at Warsaw, around the left side of Funhouse Alcove, by the walkdown gully.  The first bolt is about 15 or 20 feet up.

content.description: To the right of Tomiko on a nice gray face, start with a bolt right off the ground then trend up and right, following 7 bolts.
Directly right of the left/west walkdown.
